text:
This is the main restaurant of the Singapore Swimming Club.

We think the food quality is average esp the western meals but Asian options are pretty acceptable. The Beef Noodle soup and Char Koay Teow are good options.

Food service is slow on weekends.
Wonderful open air place to meet up with friends over drinks. Not too noisy to have a nice sit down and relax. The service was prompt and polite.
Good place to meet friends and catch up over drinks and good food.. nice ambience and good service
Food is good and service is really so so during peak times.
